==English==

===Noun===
'''harangues'''

# {{plural of|[[harangue]]}}
#:'''1875''', W. E. (William Ewart) Gladstone, '''Speeches of Pope Pius IX.''' [http://books.google.com/books?vid=LCCN09029946&id=v9V0eMfntgwC&pg=PA4&lpg=PA4&dq=harangues page 4] - ''It can hardly be policy, it must be a necessity of his nature, which prompts his incessant '''harangues'''.''
#:'''1997''', Kevin Starr, '''Endangered Dreams: The Great Depression in California''' [http://books.google.com/books?vid=ISBN0195118022&id=7GvgN0y7yI4C&pg=PA11&lpg=PA11&dq=harangues&sig=wr48Si8yy0D-_iHc5MKrCNZvYFg page 11] - ''Or perhaps Hull merely rewrote Kearney's incoherent '''harangues''', polishing their language, heightening their ferocity, after they were delivered?''


===Usage notes===
Note that the object of the plural is the speeches being made, not the number of recipients of the speech.